 To create a release notes template, you can use the `gh_list_open_issues` and `gh_get_issue` macros to fetch open issues with labels related to releases or versions. Then, you can extract the title and body of these issues to generate your release notes.

Here's an example workflow that fetches open issues with the "release" label and generates a release notes template:

```yaml
name: Generate Release Notes Template
on: [pull_request]
jobs:
  generate-template:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Checkout repository
        uses: actions/checkout@v2

      - name: Get open issues with release label
        id: get-issues
        uses: actions/github-script@v5
        with:
          script: |
            const { context } = github;
            const owner = context.repo.owner;
            const repo = context.repo.repo;
            const labelName = 'release';
            const issues = await github.issues.listForRepo({ owner, repo, labels: labelName });
            return issues.map(issue => issue.number);

      - name: Fetch release notes issues
        uses: actions/github-script@v5
        with:
          script: |
            const { context } = github;
            const owner = context.repo.owner;
            const repo = context.repo.repo;
            const issueNumbers = ${{ steps.get-issues.outputs.issue_numbers }};
            let releaseNotes = '';
            for (const number of issueNumbers) {
              const issue = await github.issues.getIssue({ owner, repo, number });
              releaseNotes += `## ${issue.title}\n\n${issue.body}\n\n`;
            }
            return releaseNotes;

      - name: Save release notes as template
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v2
        with:
          name: release-notes-template
          path: .github/RELEASE_NOTES.md
        secrets:
          GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
```

This workflow fetches open issues with the "release" label, extracts their titles and bodies, and saves them as a markdown file named `RELEASE_NOTES.md`. You can adapt this template to your specific needs by modifying the label name or adding additional formatting.

